# ESLint Configuration Rule

- Every project **must** define ESLint config (`.eslintrc.json`/`.eslintrc.js` or the new `eslint.config.js`).
- Extend the following base configs (in order):

  module.exports = {
  root: true,
  parser: "@typescript-eslint/parser",
  parserOptions: { project: "./tsconfig.json" },
  extends: [
  "eslint:recommended",
  "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
  "plugin:import/errors",
  "plugin:import/warnings",
  "plugin:import/typescript",
  "plugin:prettier/recommended"
  ],
  rules: {
  "@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars": ["error", { "argsIgnorePattern": "^_" }],
  "import/order": ["warn", { "alphabetize": { order: "asc", caseInsensitive: true } }],
  // add any project-specific rules here
  },
  };

  Add these scripts to package.json:
  {
  "scripts": {
  "lint": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx",
  "lint:fix": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx --fix"
  }
  }

Before commit or in CI, run pnpm run lint and reject if any errors remain.
